reviewText: funny movie ,bought for my son he is a collector of cheech and chong  he enjoyed all of the movies

nice dreams looks to have been digitized by a trainee, the picture quality comes and goes with each scene. Some are clear, others are very reminiscent of the drive-in, which I personally enjoy, so after a few transitions I grew to enjoy the passing low video quality. "Tough all over" is perfect, so your hi-def tv will get along fine.
 No matter what the hardcore fans won't really care and you will enjoy! I did.
Sage V.

Love Cheech & Chong movies. Bought this for my grandson and he loved it too laughed and laughed at their humor.

Well...if I am writing a review about a Cheech and Chong movie you KNOW that I obviously have all of the others(not yet, still missing 2 or 3 of them). Both good movies and got me all excited for the other ones in the series.
what can I say, it's Cheech and Chong! Funny, laughs abundant, and it's a double feature.  If you saw this in the past, watch it again and again.

all the contrast and attribution I would expect as a fan of their cinematic career. especially found of the dual movie format. much more ideal. when addressed as themselves the whole movie experience is much more engaging. not to suggest that they aren't equally convincing in supporting split roles. crude retro-grade semantics. Always good for lazy entertainment. Cheech and Chong are congenially memorable.

I'm from this generation and while I was very straight, I can still appreciate this type of humor ;)  LOVE Cheech & Chong!  I like both these movies.  Things Are Tough All Over doesn't seem to have as many fans as Nice Dreams, but I'm in the minority in that I like TATAO much better.  Glad I found this double feature.

Ok ok who doesn't love cheech and chong!?!? The previous reviews, obviously by reading them you can see they have never seen these movies. But as a cheech n chong fan of many years I'm glad I found these 2 pack deals for my husband. They came withen a couple days. Brand new in packages like stated. Works great no scratches. I do recommend this product and I am satisfied with my purchase! 5 stars!
I SAW THIS MOVIES WHEN IT FIRST CAME OUT. IT WAS FUNNY BACK THEN, BUT I GUESS WITH AGE IT ISN'T QUITE AS FUNNY AS WHEN I WAS YOUNGER.
